    VIPAN KUMAR
    3.0 out of 5 stars Good for the price
    Reviewed in India on 9 May 2022
    Verified Purchase
    Pros:
    1) Works well as advertised. Can be turned quickly and movements are smooth.
    2) Stickerless as advertised, so no hassel of stickers coming out over time.
    3) Material used is also good enough.
    4) Tension adjustment screws allow to adjust cube rotation stiffness.

    Cons:
    1) Design is not anti-pop, so blocks do come out easily when not turned properly.
    2) Edge finishing is not perfect and leaves something to be desired.
    3) Block pieces are not properly adhered and come apart easily, but can be fitted again easily. Its just that these could have been permanently glued from factory.

    My Verdict: This is a good speed cube at low price. There are better cubes with antipop design, better finishing and construction available on amazon but they go upto twice the price of this one. Although for kids I would recommend the better ones as a naughty kid will brake or rather open this into pieces with in a day, easily.

    Amazon Customer
    1.0 out of 5 stars Incorrect for solving Rubiks Cube.
    Reviewed in India on 5 July 2022
    Verified Purchase
    As a normal cube that you wanna shift and play in your hand, this is pretty good. The movement is smooth but one of the cube is sort of coming loose.
    But my main problem is the placememt of the colours. In a standard Rubiks Cube the Green centre side is opposite to the blue. This is important to create the daisy and white cross formations one has to create in the initial steps to solve the cube. In this product the green centre side in opposite to the white side. Therefore one won't be able to solve the regular way.
    There is a reason the title doesn't say Rubiks Cube. That is because that exact configuration is a trademarked product. This is a false product.
    Don't buy if you're serious about learning how to solve it.
